  <title>Clutter.Actor::button-press-event</title>
<synopsis><code mime="text/x-python">
def callback(actor, event, user_param1, ...)
</code></synopsis>
<p>The ::button-press-event signal is emitted each time a mouse button
is pressed on @actor.</p><p>or False to continue the emission.</p>

<table>
<tr>
<td><p>actor :</p></td>
<td><p>instance of Clutter.Actor that is emitting the signal</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><p>event :</p></td>
<td><p>a <link xref="Clutter.ButtonEvent">Clutter.ButtonEvent</link></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><p>user_param1 :</p></td>
<td><p>first user parameter (if any) specified with the connect() method</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><p>... :</p></td>
<td><p>additional user parameters (if any)</p></td>
</tr>
</table>
<p>Since 0.6</p>
